<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-04-1234 </DOCNO><TEXT>During the operational as well as the post-operational phase of a repositoryfor radioactive wastes, objectives have to be kept in order to protectman and environment against damage due to ionizing radiation. For theplanned Konrad repository, safety analyses are described with which thekeeping of the protection goals is examined and proved. In order to keepthese protection goals, requirements are necessary for the design ofthe plant as well as for the radioactive wastes to be disposed of.</TEXT></DOC>